1 may make a written request for an emergency absentee ballot in a
2 form prescribed by the Secretary of the State Election Board. The
3 request shall be signed by the voter and shall be provided by the
4 voter to the secretary of the county election board in the county
5 where the voter is registered. Requirements for matching of name,
6 birth date, and identification number established pursuant to
7 Section 14-105 of this title shall apply to a request for an
8 absentee ballot under this section.
9 B. Upon receipt of the voterâ€™s request, the secretary of the
10 county election board shall issue to the voter the appropriate
11 ballots and envelopes required for voting an emergency absentee
12 ballot. Provided, the voter shall present proof of identity as
13 required by Section 7-114 of this title.
14 C. The ballots must be returned in person by the voter, by
15 United States mail, or by other means of delivery approved by the
16 Secretary of the State Election Board, to the secretary of the
17 county election board no later than 7:00 p.m. on the day of the
18 election.
19 D. Upon return of the absentee ballots, the secretary of the
20 county election board shall cause the ballots to be processed in the
21 same manner as is prescribed for other absentee ballots.
22 E. The Secretary of the State Election Board shall promulgate
23 rules to implement the procedures described in this section.
24 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
